{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01E4DDU4ahZVDB1nXRDP9hZE","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 2.2: Observability Hook Enforcement\n     2→\n     3→Status: review\n     4→\n     5→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     6→\n     7→## Story\n     8→\n     9→As an operator,\n    10→I want observability coverage enforced via hooks,\n    11→so that commits below target are blocked.\n    12→\n    13→## Acceptance Criteria\n    14→\n    15→1. **Given** static coverage target is 80%, **When** current static coverage is 72%, **Then** pre-commit hook blocks with message showing current vs target. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→2. **Given** both static and runtime coverage pass targets, **When** commit is attempted, **Then** hook allows it. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→3. **Given** hook blocks, **When** the message is displayed, **Then** it includes specific files/functions missing logging and how to fix. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→\n    19→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    20→\n    21→- [x] Task 1: Add observability coverage check function to `src/modules/observability/coverage.ts` (AC: #1, #2)\n    22→  - [x]1.1: Implement `checkObservabilityCoverageGate(projectDir: string): Result<ObservabilityCoverageGateResult>` that reads both static and runtime coverage from `sprint-state.json` and compares against targets\n    23→  - [x]1.2: Define `ObservabilityCoverageGateResult` type in `types.ts` with fields: `passed: boolean`, `staticResult: CoverageTargetResult`, `runtimeResult: CoverageTargetResult | null`, `gapSummary: ObservabilityGap[]`\n    24→  - [x]1.3: When runtime coverage state is absent (no verification run yet), skip runtime check and pass that dimension — only static is required for commit gate\n    25→  - [x]1.4: Export the new function and type from `src/modules/observability/index.ts`\n    26→\n    27→- [x] Task 2: Add CLI subcommand `codeharness observability-gate` (AC: #1, #2, #3)\n    28→  - [x]2.1: Create `src/commands/observability-gate.ts` implementing the gate check callable from shell\n    29→  - [x]2.2: Accept `--json` flag for machine-readable output (used by hook script)\n    30→  - [x]2.3: Accept `--min-static <N>` and `--min-runtime <N>` optional overrides (default: read from `sprint-state.json` targets)\n    31→  - [x]2.4: On pass: exit 0, print summary. On fail: exit 1, print current vs target and gap details\n    32→  - [x]2.5: Wire into CLI entry point (`src/cli.ts` or equivalent command registry)\n    33→\n    34→- [x] Task 3: Update `hooks/pre-commit-gate.sh` to call observability gate (AC: #1, #2, #3)\n    35→  - [x]3.1: After existing quality gate checks (tests_passed, coverage_met, verification_run), add observability coverage check section\n    36→  - [x]3.2: Call `${HARNESS_CLI} observability-gate --json` and parse the JSON result\n    37→  - [x]3.3: If gate fails, build block message with: current static % vs target %, gap file/function list, and fix suggestion (\"add logging to these functions, then run `codeharness analyze`\")\n    38→  - [x]3.4: If `${HARNESS_CLI}` is not available or observability-gate command fails, fail open (allow commit) — consistent with existing hook pattern\n    39→  - [x]3.5: Ensure total hook execution stays within 500ms NFR — use `timeout` wrapper if needed on the CLI call\n    40→\n    41→- [x] Task 4: Include gap details in hook block message (AC: #3)\n    42→  - [x]4.1: The `observability-gate --json` output must include `gaps[]` array with `{ file, line, type, description }` per gap\n    43→  - [x]4.2: Hook formats top 5 gaps as `file:line — description` lines in the block reason\n    44→  - [x]4.3: If more than 5 gaps, append `... and N more. Run: codeharness analyze` to see all\n    45→  - [x]4.4: Include fix suggestion: \"Add logging to flagged functions. See: patches/observability/ for rule definitions\"\n    46→\n    47→- [x] Task 5: Write unit tests (AC: all)\n    48→  - [x]5.1: Create `src/modules/observability/__tests__/coverage-gate.test.ts`:\n    49→    - Test gate passes when static >= 80% and runtime >= 60%\n    50→    - Test gate fails when static is 72% (below 80% target)\n    51→    - Test gate passes when runtime is absent (no verification yet)\n    52→    - Test gate fails when runtime is 50% (below 60% target)\n    53→    - Test gate returns gap list with file/line/description\n    54→    - Test custom target overrides work\n    55→  - [x]5.2: Create `src/commands/__tests__/observability-gate.test.ts`:\n    56→    - Test `--json` output format matches expected schema\n    57→    - Test exit code 0 on pass, exit code 1 on fail\n    58→    - Test `--min-static` override\n    59→  - [x]5.3: Create `test/hooks/pre-commit-gate-observability.bats` (BATS integration test):\n    60→    - Test hook allows commit when observability passes\n    61→    - Test hook blocks commit when observability fails\n    62→    - Test hook fails open when CLI not available\n    63→  - [x]5.4: Mock all filesystem operations in unit tests — no real I/O\n    64→  - [x]5.5: Target 100% coverage on all new files\n    65→\n    66→- [x] Task 6: Integration verification (AC: all)\n    67→  - [x]6.1: Run `npm run build` — verify tsup compiles new module\n    68→  - [x]6.2: Run `npm run test:unit` — all tests pass\n    69→  - [x]6.3: Verify module boundaries: only barrel index.ts exports public API\n    70→  - [x]6.4: Verify no file exceeds 300 lines (NFR9)\n    71→  - [x]6.5: Verify hook total execution time stays under 500ms (NFR1)\n    72→\n    73→## Dev Notes\n    74→\n    75→### Architecture References\n    76→\n    77→This story implements FR11 (enforce observability coverage target via hooks) and FR12 (track observability coverage trend in state file — already done in Stories 1.3 and 2.1).\n    78→\n    79→Architecture Decision 2 (Separate Metrics) applies: static and runtime coverage are checked independently against separate targets. Both must pass for the gate to allow commit.\n    80→\n    81→### Key Implementation Details\n    82→\n    83→**Hook integration approach:** The existing `hooks/pre-commit-gate.sh` already blocks commits when quality gates fail (`tests_passed`, `coverage_met`, `verification_run`). This story adds an observability coverage check as an additional gate after those existing checks. The hook calls a CLI command (not direct state file reads) because computing gaps requires the analyzer module.\n    84→\n    85→**Two-tier gate:** Static coverage is always checked (analyzer can run anytime). Runtime coverage is only checked when runtime state exists in `sprint-state.json` (i.e., after at least one verification run). This prevents blocking commits in projects that haven't run verification yet.\n    86→\n    87→**CLI command pattern:** Follow the existing `codeharness coverage --check-only` pattern (see `pre-commit-gate.sh` lines 78-87). The new `codeharness observability-gate` command reads state, computes result, exits with appropriate code.\n    88→\n    89→**Gap details:** The `checkObservabilityCoverageGate` function should call `readCoverageState()` to get current coverage and targets, then call `analyze()` to get the current gap list. The gap list is what gives the developer actionable information (file, line, rule, description).\n    90→\n    91→**Performance concern:** Running `semgrep scan` in the hook could exceed 500ms NFR for large projects. Two options: (1) use cached analyzer results from `sprint-state.json` instead of re-running Semgrep, or (2) gate only on cached coverage % and show gap details only in the detailed report. Prefer option 1 (cached results) for the hook — the hook checks the coverage number from state; the full analyzer run happens during `codeharness analyze` or code review.\n    92→\n    93→**Revised approach for hook performance:** The hook should NOT re-run Semgrep. Instead:\n    94→1. Read `observability.static.coveragePercent` from `sprint-state.json`\n    95→2. Read `observability.runtime.coveragePercent` from `sprint-state.json`\n    96→3. Compare against `observability.targets.staticTarget` and `observability.targets.runtimeTarget`\n    97→4. If below target, the block message says \"Run `codeharness analyze` to see gaps\" — the gap list comes from the analyzer, not the hook\n    98→5. This keeps the hook well under 500ms\n    99→\n   100→**State file locations:**\n   101→- `sprint-state.json` — observability coverage state (static, runtime, targets)\n   102→- `.claude/codeharness.local.md` — session flags (tests_passed, coverage_met, etc.) — NOT used for observability coverage\n   103→\n   104→### Existing Code to Reuse\n   105→\n   106→- `src/modules/observability/coverage.ts` — `readCoverageState()`, `checkCoverageTarget()` — reuse for static check\n   107→- `src/modules/observability/types.ts` — `ObservabilityCoverageState`, `CoverageTargetResult`, `CoverageTargets`\n   108→- `hooks/pre-commit-gate.sh` — extend with observability gate call\n   109→- `src/modules/observability/index.ts` — barrel to update with new exports\n   110→\n   111→### What This Story Does NOT Include\n   112→\n   113→- No re-running Semgrep in the hook — uses cached coverage from state file\n   114→- No standalone runtime check outside verification — that's Story 2.3\n   115→- No audit integration — that's Epic 3\n   116→- No code review integration — that's Story 5.1\n   117→- No combined metric — static and runtime are always separate (Decision 2)\n   118→\n   119→### Dependencies\n   120→\n   121→- **Depends on:** Story 1.3 (static coverage state tracking and `readCoverageState`) — DONE\n   122→- **Depends on:** Story 2.1 (runtime coverage state and `saveRuntimeCoverage`) — DONE\n   123→- **Depends on:** Story 1.2 (analyzer module for gap details via `analyze()`) — DONE\n   124→- **Depended on by:** Story 5.1 (code review observability check), Story 3.1 (audit coordinator)\n   125→\n   126→### File Size Constraint\n   127→\n   128→Each new file must be under 300 lines per NFR9. `observability-gate.ts` command should be ~80 lines. Gate function addition to `coverage.ts` should be ~40 lines. Hook additions should be ~30 lines within existing file.\n   129→\n   130→### Existing Relevant Code\n   131→\n   132→- `hooks/pre-commit-gate.sh` — hook to extend (currently 90 lines)\n   133→- `src/modules/observability/coverage.ts` — coverage read/check functions (currently 269 lines — close to limit, consider new file if needed)\n   134→- `src/modules/observability/types.ts` — types to extend with gate result type\n   135→- `src/modules/observability/index.ts` — barrel to update\n   136→- `src/types/result.ts` — Result<T> pattern used by all modules\n   137→\n   138→### References\n   139→\n   140→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md#Decision 2] -- Separate metrics, enforcement via hooks\n   141→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md#Decision 1] -- Semgrep static analysis\n   142→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-operational-excellence.md#Story 2.2] -- Acceptance criteria and user story\n   143→- [Source: hooks/pre-commit-gate.sh] -- Existing pre-commit hook pattern\n   144→- [Source: src/modules/observability/coverage.ts] -- readCoverageState, checkCoverageTarget\n   145→- [Source: src/modules/observability/types.ts] -- CoverageTargetResult, ObservabilityCoverageState\n   146→\n   147→### Previous Story Intelligence (Story 2.1)\n   148→\n   149→- **Atomic write pattern:** `runtime-coverage.ts` uses read-modify-write with temp+rename. Same pattern for any state updates.\n   150→- **Barrel imports only:** Story 2.1 had a bug importing from internal file (`../verify/types.js`) instead of barrel (`../verify/index.js`). Always import from barrel.\n   151→- **VerifyResult extension:** Story 2.1 added `observabilityGapCount` and `runtimeCoveragePercent` to `VerifyResult`. All existing constructions had to be updated. Watch for similar when extending types.\n   152→- **Mock all I/O:** All filesystem operations mocked in unit tests. No real file reads/writes.\n   153→- **File under 150 lines:** `runtime-coverage.ts` is 112 lines. Keep new files similarly lean.\n   154→\n   155→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   156→## Verification Requirements\n   157→\n   158→- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/2-2-observability-hook-enforcement.proof.md`)\n   159→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n   160→- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100% of all new code in src/)\n   161→\n   162→## Documentation Requirements\n   163→\n   164→- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (src/modules/observability/AGENTS.md, src/commands/AGENTS.md)\n   165→- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/2-2-observability-hook-enforcement.md`\n   166→\n   167→## Testing Requirements\n   168→\n   169→- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   170→- [ ] BATS integration test for hook behavior\n   171→- [ ] Filesystem operations mocked (no real I/O in unit tests)\n   172→- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n   173→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   174→\n   175→## Dev Agent Record\n   176→\n   177→### Agent Model Used\n   178→\n   179→Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n   180→\n   181→### Debug Log References\n   182→\n   183→None.\n   184→\n   185→### Completion Notes List\n   186→\n   187→- All 6 tasks implemented and verified\n   188→- Build passes, all 2614 unit tests pass, 4 BATS integration tests pass\n   189→- coverage.ts extended with runtime parsing (was missing), now 296 lines (under 300 NFR9)\n   190→- coverage-gate.ts: 82 lines, observability-gate.ts: 84 lines, hook additions: ~24 lines\n   191→\n   192→### File List\n   193→\n   194→- `src/modules/observability/coverage-gate.ts` (NEW) — gate check function\n   195→- `src/modules/observability/types.ts` (MODIFIED) — added `ObservabilityCoverageGateResult` type\n   196→- `src/modules/observability/coverage.ts` (MODIFIED) — extended `extractCoverageState` with runtime + runtimeTarget parsing\n   197→- `src/modules/observability/index.ts` (MODIFIED) — barrel exports for new type and function\n   198→- `src/commands/observability-gate.ts` (NEW) — CLI command\n   199→- `src/index.ts` (MODIFIED) — registered new command (22 total)\n   200→- `hooks/pre-commit-gate.sh` (MODIFIED) — observability gate section added\n   201→- `src/modules/observability/__tests__/coverage-gate.test.ts` (NEW) — 14 unit tests\n   202→- `src/commands/__tests__/observability-gate.test.ts` (NEW) — 21 unit tests\n   203→- `src/__tests__/cli.test.ts` (MODIFIED) — updated command count to 22\n   204→- `tests/observability_gate_hook.bats` (NEW) — 4 BATS integration tests\n   205→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01L7x1Zkv5Yv1DsfgSndzqDQ","session_id":"f7a66acd-0cc1-40de-a592-d59e75273c0b","uuid":"f9a75cba-5978-4d3c-b492-97f5b567e6ff","timestamp":"2026-03-20T05:59:58.915Z"}
