{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Y3xxTruVWkU4AxMahscDzG","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Observability Module\n     2→\n     3→Static analysis of observability coverage (logging gaps, error handler coverage) and coverage state tracking over time.\n     4→\n     5→## Files\n     6→\n     7→- `index.ts` — Public API barrel: re-exports `analyze` from analyzer, `saveCoverageResult`, `readCoverageState`, `getCoverageTrend`, `checkCoverageTarget` from coverage, and all public types.\n     8→- `analyzer.ts` — Static analysis runner: `analyze(projectDir, config?)` — runs Semgrep (or skips gracefully if not installed), parses results into tool-agnostic `AnalyzerResult`. Also exports `checkSemgrepInstalled`, `runSemgrep`, `parseSemgrepOutput`, `computeSummary`.\n     9→- `coverage.ts` — Coverage state persistence: `saveCoverageResult(projectDir, result)` — writes coverage to sprint-state.json atomically, appends to history. `readCoverageState(projectDir)` — reads typed coverage state. `getCoverageTrend(projectDir)` — compares latest vs previous history entry. `checkCoverageTarget(projectDir, target?)` — checks coverage against target (default 80%).\n    10→- `types.ts` — All interfaces: `AnalyzerResult`, `AnalyzerConfig`, `AnalyzerSummary`, `ObservabilityGap`, `GapSeverity`, `SemgrepRawOutput`, `SemgrepResult`, `ObservabilityCoverageState`, `StaticCoverageState`, `CoverageTargets`, `CoverageHistoryEntry`, `CoverageTrend`, `CoverageTargetResult`.\n    11→\n    12→## Patterns\n    13→\n    14→- All public functions return `Result<T>` (never throw)\n    15→- Atomic writes via temp file + `renameSync` (same pattern as sprint/state.ts)\n    16→- ES module imports with `.js` extensions\n    17→- Coverage state stored in `sprint-state.json` under `observability` key\n    18→- Only `static` coverage section implemented; `runtime` deferred to Epic 2\n    19→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01L7x1Zkv5Yv1DsfgSndzqDQ","session_id":"f7a66acd-0cc1-40de-a592-d59e75273c0b","uuid":"1a605b3a-6a52-4551-a88d-d2a6f8a162ae","timestamp":"2026-03-20T06:02:37.665Z"}
