out` command in `pre-commit-gate.sh` not available on stock macOS. The observability gate check silently never ran on Mac, failing open without warning. Fixed.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt):**\n- **LOW** — Grep-based JSON parsing in `pre-commit-gate.sh` (lines 93-99) is fragile; a JSON field order change or nested structure change could extract wrong values. This is a pre-existing pattern used for the per-file coverage check too, so fixing it would be a broader refactor.\n- **LOW** — `coverage-gate.ts` line 47 fallback to `DEFAULT_STATIC_TARGET` is unreachable because `extractCoverageState` always returns a default `staticTarget`. The fallback `??` is defensive but dead code.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- `observability-gate.ts` line 35 (JSON error output for `--min-runtime` with `--json` flag) is not directly covered. The identical code path for `--min-static` + `--json` IS covered. Acceptable.\n- `coverage-gate.ts` branch coverage at 95.23% — the `DEFAULT_STATIC_TARGET` fallback on line 47 is unreachable (see LOW above).\n- Missing Showboat proof document at `docs/exec-plans/active/2-2-observability-hook-enforcement.proof.md` — required by story verification checklist but not created by dev agent.\n- BATS integration tests do not test the actual observability gate blocking behavior (only tests fail-open with no CLI and existing quality gate blocking).\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. The implementation follows the barrel-only import pattern, uses `Result<T>` consistently, and the hook stays within the existing pattern of calling CLI commands.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues have been fixed."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a8592e633ed052299 (use SendMessage with to: 'a8592e633ed052299' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 69471\ntool_uses: 65\nduration_ms: 329205</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f7a66acd-0cc1-40de-a592-d59e75273c0b","uuid":