{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Dv3SY75PG4ytrgYfYz7GTc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 2.2: Observability Hook Enforcement — Verification Proof\n     2→\n     3→**Verified:** 2026-03-20\n     4→**Verifier:** Claude Opus 4.6 (black-box)\n     5→**Container:** `codeharness-verify`\n     6→**CLI Version:** 0.21.1\n     7→\n     8→---\n     9→\n    10→## AC 1: Given static coverage target is 80%, When current static coverage is 72%, Then pre-commit hook blocks with message showing current vs target\n    11→\n    12→**Status: PASS**\n    13→\n    14→### Setup — Create sprint-state.json with 72% static coverage\n    15→\n    16→```bash\n    17→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /tmp/test-project && cat > sprint-state.json << EOF\n    18→{\n    19→  \"observability\": {\n    20→    \"static\": {\n    21→      \"coveragePercent\": 72,\n    22→      \"totalFunctions\": 100,\n    23→      \"coveredFunctions\": 72\n    24→    },\n    25→    \"runtime\": null,\n    26→    \"targets\": {\n    27→      \"staticTarget\": 80,\n    28→      \"runtimeTarget\": 60\n    29→    }\n    30→  }\n    31→}\n    32→EOF'\n    33→```\n    34→\n    35→### Test — Run observability-gate (human-readable output)\n    36→\n    37→```bash\n    38→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /tmp/test-project && codeharness observability-gate 2>&1; echo \"EXIT:$?\"'\n    39→```\n    40→\n    41→```output\n    42→[FAIL] Observability gate failed. Static: 72% / 80% target\n    43→[FAIL] Run `codeharness analyze` to see gaps and fix suggestions.\n    44→EXIT:1\n    45→```\n    46→\n    47→### Test — Run observability-gate (JSON output)\n    48→\n    49→```bash\n    50→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /tmp/test-project && codeharness observability-gate --json 2>&1; echo \"EXIT:$?\"'\n    51→```\n    52→\n    53→```output\n    54→{\"status\":\"fail\",\"passed\":false,\"static\":{\"current\":72,\"target\":80,\"met\":false,\"gap\":8},\"runtime\":null,\"gaps\":[]}\n    55→EXIT:1\n    56→```\n    57→\n    58→### Evidence\n    59→\n    60→- Exit code is **1** (non-zero) — blocks the commit gate.\n    61→- Human-readable output shows `Static: 72% / 80% target` — current vs target displayed.\n    62→- JSON output includes `\"current\":72,\"target\":80,\"met\":false,\"gap\":8`.\n    63→\n    64→[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction — VictoriaLogs returned empty results for all queries during verification.\n    65→\n    66→---\n    67→\n    68→## AC 2: Given both static and runtime coverage pass targets, When commit is attempted, Then hook allows it\n    69→\n    70→**Status: PASS**\n    71→\n    72→### Setup — Create sprint-state.json with both metrics passing\n    73→\n    74→```bash\n    75→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /tmp/test-project && cat > sprint-state.json << EOF\n    76→{\n    77→  \"observability\": {\n    78→    \"static\": {\n    79→      \"coveragePercent\": 85,\n    80→      \"totalFunctions\": 100,\n    81→      \"coveredFunctions\": 85\n    82→    },\n    83→    \"runtime\": {\n    84→      \"coveragePercent\": 75,\n    85→      \"totalEndpoints\": 50,\n    86→      \"coveredEndpoints\": 38\n    87→    },\n    88→    \"targets\": {\n    89→      \"staticTarget\": 80,\n    90→      \"runtimeTarget\": 60\n    91→    }\n    92→  }\n    93→}\n    94→EOF'\n    95→```\n    96→\n    97→### Test — Run observability-gate (human-readable output)\n    98→\n    99→```bash\n   100→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /tmp/test-project && codeharness observability-gate 2>&1; echo \"EXIT:$?\"'\n   101→```\n   102→\n   103→```output\n   104→[OK] Observability gate passed. Static: 85% / 80% target\n   105→[OK] Runtime: 75% / 60% target\n   106→EXIT:0\n   107→```\n   108→\n   109→### Test — Run observability-gate (JSON output)\n   110→\n   111→```bash\n   112→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /tmp/test-project && codeharness observability-gate --json 2>&1'\n   113→```\n   114→\n   115→```output\n   116→{\"status\":\"pass\",\"passed\":true,\"static\":{\"current\":85,\"target\":80,\"met\":true,\"gap\":0},\"runtime\":{\"current\":75,\"target\":60,\"met\":true,\"gap\":0},\"gaps\":[]}\n   117→```\n   118→\n   119→### Evidence\n   120→\n   121→- Exit code is **0** — allows the commit.\n   122→- Both static (85% >= 80%) and runtime (75% >= 60%) are met.\n   123→- JSON confirms `\"passed\":true`, both dimensions show `\"met\":true`.\n   124→\n   125→### Supplementary — Override targets via CLI flags\n   126→\n   127→```bash\n   128→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /tmp/test-project && codeharness observability-gate --min-static 70 --json 2>&1; echo \"EXIT:$?\"'\n   129→```\n   130→\n   131→```output\n   132→{\"status\":\"pass\",\"passed\":true,\"static\":{\"current\":72,\"target\":70,\"met\":true,\"gap\":0},\"runtime\":null,\"gaps\":[]}\n   133→EXIT:0\n   134→```\n   135→\n   136→This confirms the `--min-static` override flag works as designed.\n   137→\n   138→[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction.\n   139→\n   140→---\n   141→\n   142→## AC 3: Given hook blocks, When the message is displayed, Then it includes specific files/functions missing logging and how to fix\n   143→\n   144→**Status: FAIL**\n   145→\n   146→### Test — Block message content\n   147→\n   148→```bash\n   149→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /tmp/test-project && codeharness observability-gate 2>&1'\n   150→```\n   151→\n   152→```output\n   153→[FAIL] Observability gate failed. Static: 72% / 80% target\n   154→[FAIL] Run `codeharness analyze` to see gaps and fix suggestions.\n   155→```\n   156→\n   157→### Test — JSON output gaps array\n   158→\n   159→```bash\n   160→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /tmp/test-project && codeharness observability-gate --json 2>&1'\n   161→```\n   162→\n   163→```output\n   164→{\"status\":\"fail\",\"passed\":false,\"static\":{\"current\":72,\"target\":80,\"met\":false,\"gap\":8},\"runtime\":null,\"gaps\":[]}\n   165→```\n   166→\n   167→### Root Cause — Built artifact inspection\n   168→\n   169→The built artifact at `/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js` lines 5289-5290 shows:\n   170→\n   171→```bash\n   172→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'sed -n \"5289,5290p\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js'\n   173→```\n   174→\n   175→```output\n   176→  const gapSummary = [];\n   177→  return ok2({ passed, staticResult, runtimeResult, gapSummary });\n   178→```\n   179→\n   180→The `checkObservabilityCoverageGate` function hardcodes `gapSummary = []` — it never reads gap data from `sprint-state.json` nor calls any analyzer function. The output formatting code (line 10863) correctly maps `gate.gapSummary` to the `gaps` JSON field, but since the source array is always empty, no gaps are ever displayed.\n   181→\n   182→### What AC 3 requires vs what is delivered\n   183→\n   184→| Requirement | Delivered |\n   185→|---|---|\n   186→| Specific files/functions missing logging | **Not delivered** — `gaps` array is always `[]` |\n   187→| How to fix | **Partially delivered** — message says `Run codeharness analyze to see gaps and fix suggestions` |\n   188→\n   189→The block message provides a **pointer** to how to find gaps (`codeharness analyze`) but does NOT include the specific files/functions inline as AC 3 requires. Furthermore, there is no `codeharness analyze` CLI command — it does not appear in `codeharness --help`.\n   190→\n   191→### Task 4 implementation gap\n   192→\n   193→Per story Task 4:\n   194→- Task 4.1: \"The observability-gate --json output must include gaps[] array\" — **Not met** (always empty)\n   195→- Task 4.2: \"Hook formats top 5 gaps as file:line — description\" — **Not met** (no gaps to format)\n   196→- Task 4.3: \"If more than 5 gaps, append ... and N more\" — **Not met**\n   197→- Task 4.4: \"Include fix suggestion\" — **Partially met** (generic pointer, not specific)\n   198→\n   199→[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction.\n   200→\n   201→---\n   202→\n   203→## Summary\n   204→\n   205→| AC | Status | Notes |\n   206→|---|---|---|\n   207→| AC 1 | **PASS** | Blocks with exit 1, shows 72% vs 80% target |\n   208→| AC 2 | **PASS** | Allows with exit 0, both static and runtime verified |\n   209→| AC 3 | **FAIL** | `gapSummary` hardcoded as empty array; no specific files/functions shown in block message |\n   210→\n   211→## Observability Notes\n   212→\n   213→VictoriaLogs at `localhost:9428` returned no log entries for any CLI command execution during this verification session. The CLI does not appear to emit structured logs to the observability stack during `observability-gate` execution.\n   214→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f7a66acd-0cc1-40de-a592-d59e75273c0b","uuid":"35ba2633-498a-4b6f-9a24-95f9b942792b","timestamp":"2026-03-20T06:11:06.914Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/verification/2-2-observability-hook-enforcement-proof.md","content":"# Story 2.2: Observability Hook Enforcement — Verification Proof\n\n**Verified:** 2026-03-20\n**Verifier:** Claude Opus 4.6 (black-box)\n**Container:** `codeharness-verify`\n**CLI Version:** 0.21.1\n\n---\n\n## AC 1: Given static coverage target is 80%, When current static coverage is 72%, Then pre-commit hook blocks with message showing current vs target\n\n**Status: PASS**\n\n### Setup — Create sprint-state.json with 72% static coverage\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /tmp/test-project && cat > sprint-state.json << EOF\n{\n  \"observability\": {\n    \"static\": {\n      \"coveragePercent\": 72,\n      \"totalFunctions\": 100,\n      \"coveredFunctions\": 72\n    },\n    \"runtime\": null,\n    \"targets\": {\n      \"staticTarget\": 80,\n      \"runtimeTarget\": 60\n    }\n  }\n}\nEOF'\n```\n\n### Test — Run observability-gate (human-readable output)\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /tmp/test-project && codeharness observability-gate 2>&1; echo \"EXIT:$?\"'\n```\n\n```output\n[FAIL] Observability gate failed. Static: 72% / 80% target\n[FAIL] Run `codeharness analyze` to see gaps and fix suggestions.\nEXIT:1\n```\n\n### Test — Run observability-gate (JSON output)\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /tmp/test-project && codeharness observability-gate --json 2>&1; echo \"EXIT:$?\"'\n```\n\n```output\n{\"status\":\"fail\",\"passed\":false,\"static\":{\"current\":72,\"target\":80,\"met\":false,\"gap\":8},\"runtime\":null,\"gaps\":[]}\nEXIT:1\n```\n\n### Evidence\n\n- Exit code is **1** (non-zero) — blocks the commit gate.\n- Human-readable output shows `Static: 72% / 80% target` — current vs target displayed.\n- JSON output includes `\"current\":72,\"target\":80,\"met\":false,\"gap\":8`.\n\n[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction — VictoriaLogs returned empty results for all queries during verification.\n\n---\n\n## AC 2: Given both static and runtime coverage pass targets, When commit is attempted, Then hook allows it\n\n**Status: PASS**\n\n### Setup — Create sprint-state.json with both metrics passing\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /tmp/test-project && cat > sprint-state.json << EOF\n{\n  \"observability\": {\n    \"static\": {\n      \"coveragePercent\": 85,\n      \"totalFunctions\": 100,\n      \"coveredFunctions\": 85\n    },\n    \"runtime\": {\n      \"coveragePercent\": 75,\n      \"totalEndpoints\": 50,\n      \"coveredEndpoints\": 38\n    },\n    \"targets\": {\n      \"staticTarget\": 80,\n      \"runtimeTarget\": 60\n    }\n  }\n}\nEOF'\n```\n\n### Test — Run observability-gate (human-readable output)\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /tmp/test-project && codeharness observability-gate 2>&1; echo \"EXIT:$?\"'\n```\n\n```output\n[OK] Observability gate passed. Static: 85% / 80% target\n[OK] Runtime: 75% / 60% target\nEXIT:0\n```\n\n### Test — Run observability-gate (JSON output)\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /tmp/test-project && codeharness observability-gate --json 2>&1'\n```\n\n```output\n{\"status\":\"pass\",\"passed\":true,\"static\":{\"current\":85,\"target\":80,\"met\":true,\"gap\":0},\"runtime\":{\"current\":75,\"target\":60,\"met\":true,\"gap\":0},\"gaps\":[]}\n```\n\n### Evidence\n\n- Exit code is **0** — allows the commit.\n- Both static (85% >= 80%) and runtime (75% >= 60%) are met.\n- JSON confirms `\"passed\":true`, both dimensions show `\"met\":true`.\n\n### Supplementary — Override targets via CLI flags\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /tmp/test-project && codeharness observability-gate --min-static 70 --json 2>&1; echo \"EXIT:$?\"'\n```\n\n```output\n{\"status\":\"pass\",\"passed\":true,\"static\":{\"current\":72,\"target\":70,\"met\":true,\"gap\":0},\"runtime\":null,\"gaps\":[]}\nEXIT:0\n```\n\nThis confirms the `--min-static` override flag works as designed.\n\n[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction.\n\n---\n\n## AC 3: Given hook blocks, When the message is displayed, Then it includes specific files/functions missing logging and how to fix\n\n**Status: FAIL**\n\n### Test — Block message content\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /tmp/test-project && codeharness observability-gate 2>&1'\n```\n\n```output\n[FAIL] Observability gate failed. Static: 72% / 80% target\n[FAIL] Run `codeharness analyze` to see gaps and fix suggestions.\n```\n\n### Test — JSON output gaps array\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /tmp/test-project && codeharness observability-gate --json 2>&1'\n```\n\n```output\n{\"status\":\"fail\",\"passed\":false,\"static\":{\"current\":72,\"target\":80,\"met\":false,\"gap\":8},\"runtime\":null,\"gaps\":[]}\n```\n\n### Root Cause — Built artifact inspection\n\nThe built artifact at `/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js` lines 5289-5290 shows:\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'sed -n \"5289,5290p\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js'\n```\n\n```output\n  const gapSummary = [];\n  return ok2({ passed, staticResult, runtimeResult, gapSummary });\n```\n\nThe `checkObservabilityCoverageGate` function hardcodes `gapSummary = []` — it never reads gap data from `sprint-state.json` nor calls any analyzer function. The output formatting code (line 10863) correctly maps `gate.gapSummary` to the `gaps` JSON field, but since the source array is always empty, no gaps are ever displayed.\n\n### What AC 3 requires vs what is delivered\n\n| Requirement | Delivered |\n|---|---|\n| Specific files/functions missing logging | **Not delivered** — `gaps` array is always `[]` |\n| How to fix | **Partially delivered** — message says `Run codeharness analyze to see gaps and fix suggestions` |\n\nThe block message provides a **pointer** to how to find gaps (`codeharness analyze`) but does NOT include the specific files/functions inline as AC 3 requires. Furthermore, there is no `codeharness analyze` CLI command — it does not appear in `codeharness --help`.\n\n### Task 4 implementation gap\n\nPer story Task 4:\n- Task 4.1: \"The observability-gate --json output must include gaps[] array\" — **Not met** (always empty)\n- Task 4.2: \"Hook formats top 5 gaps as file:line — description\" — **Not met** (no gaps to format)\n- Task 4.3: \"If more than 5 gaps, append ... and N more\" — **Not met**\n- Task 4.4: \"Include fix suggestion\" — **Partially met** (generic pointer, not specific)\n\n[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| AC | Status | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| AC 1 | **PASS** | Blocks with exit 1, shows 72% vs 80% target |\n| AC 2 | **PASS** | Allows with exit 0, both static and runtime verified |\n| AC 3 | **FAIL** | `gapSummary` hardcoded as empty array; no specific files/functions shown in block message |\n\n## Observability Notes\n\nVictoriaLogs at `localhost:9428` returned no log entries for any CLI command execution during this verification session. The CLI does not appear to emit structured logs to the observability stack during `observability-gate` execution.\n","numLines":214,"startLine":1,"totalLines":214}}}
