ntime data. Extended it — technically a bug fix for Story 2.1.\",\n   228→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   229→      \"resolved\": false\n   230→    },\n   231→    {\n   232→      \"id\": \"migrated-3\",\n   233→      \"story\": \"2-2-observability-hook-enforcement\",\n   234→      \"description\": \"**Gap details limited in hook:** Hook directs users to run `codeharness analyze` instead of showing file/line details (Semgrep too slow for hook context).\",\n   235→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   236→      \"resolved\": false\n   237→    },\n   238→    {\n   239→      \"id\": \"migrated-4\",\n   240→      \"story\": \"2-2-observability-hook-enforcement\",\n   241→      \"description\": \"**sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent** — updated manually by harness-run.\",\n   242→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   243→      \"resolved\": false\n   244→    },\n   245→    {\n   246→      \"id\": \"migrated-5\",\n   247→      \"story\": \"2-2-observability-hook-enforcement\",\n   248→      \"description\": \"**Ambiguity in AC 3:** Epic says block message should include specific files/functions missing logging. Getting specific gaps requires running Semgrep (~10s), violating 500ms hook NFR. Story resolves by using cached coverage and directing user to `codeharness analyze`.\",\n   249→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   250→      \"resolved\": false\n   251→    },\n   252→    {\n   253→      \"id\": \"migrated-6\",\n   254→      \"story\": \"2-2-observability-hook-enforcement\",\n   255→      \"description\": \"**Risk: `coverage.ts` line limit.** Existing file is 269 lines; adding gate function (~40 lines) may exceed 300-line NFR9 limit.\",\n   256→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   257→      \"resolved\": false\n   258→    },\n   259→    {\n   260→      \"id\": \"migrated-7\",\n   261→      \"story\": \"2-2-observability-hook-enforcement\",\n   262→      \"description\": \"**No `codeharness analyze` CLI command exists yet.** Story references it in error messages but no such subcom